<i>Posted by Arich on 09-27-2003 11:10 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Cupric Sulfate Pentahydrate is what it would be called.  I've worked with this stuff a bit in lab.<br />
<br />
Plaz is correct.  When you heat the substance, the water breaks away of the CuSO4 and you get the base substance.  The water evaporates and you just have the pure CuSO4.  Not sure if it's a white powder, but you can put water back into the molecular structure and it will react to turn blue again.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
